    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i was just looking at some photos from the james webb telescope and it just hit me... everything we do, every single thing, is literally nothing. the universe is so huge and old and just... indifferent. it feels like we're just tiny mistakes in a void that doesn't even care we exist. makes everything feel so pointless.",
